Investing in Shiba Inu (SHIB) – Everything You Need to Know

SHIB is the latest breakout meme token to capture the interests of the blockchain investment community. This token is seen by many as a knock-off of the Dogecoin in that it also borrows inspiration from the famed $SHIB

SHIB token is our first token and allows users to hold Billions or even Trillions of them, the official website mentions. More additions are coming up as per the Shiba Inu’s website. The creators plan to launch Bone Dogecoin Killer, the next coin in future.

How different is Shiba Inu?

Dogecoin has been developed using the same technology as Bitcoin. Shiba Inu tokens are powered by Ethereum. Fungible tokens like Shiba Inu are ERC-20 tokens and non-fungible tokens (NFTs) use the ERC-721 token standard of the Ethereum platform.

Who owns Shiba Inu?

The owner of Shiba Inu is someone named Ryoshi though no one knows this person’s actual name. The meme coin has been named after the Japanese dog breed, Shiba. Incidentally, Shiba had claimed they are the ‘Dogecoin Killer’ when it was launched in August 2020
